    <div class="lesson-content-title col-xs-12">E=mc<sup>2</sup> as a Conversion between Units</div>
  <div class="lesson-content-body col-xs-12 ">

      <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          <div class="lesson-content-memo"> Mass or energy </div>   

          The speed of light is a constant, 
          so one way to regard E=mc<sup>2</sup> is as a conversion between units of mass and energy.
          Mass is a form of energy, so 
          in energy conservation calculations, the rest mass energy has to be included.
         <br/><br/>
         All these statements are equivalent:
         <ul>
             <li>There are 9 x 10<sup>16</sup> J in 1 kg</li>
             <li>In 1g there are 9 x 10<sup>13</sup> J</li>
             <li>(J/kg) = 9 x 10<sup>16</sup></li>
         </ul>
         
         
